properties.areaDesc: West Side Hills; Western San Joaquin Valley; San Joaquin Confluence
properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 29 at 10:00PM PST until March 1 at 4:00AM PST by NWS Hanford CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Sustained west winds 15 to 25 mph, with gusts around 45
mph expected.

* WHERE...Areas around the San Joaquin River and east of
Interstate 5 from Mendota to Newman, Western San Joaquin Valley
south of Mendota to the Tulare Lake Bed, and West Side Hills.

* WHEN...Until 4 AM PST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects.
Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may
result. Travel can be difficult, especially for high profile
vehicles such as campers and tractor trailers.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Highways affected include, but are not
limited to Highway 198, Highway 180, Interstate 5 north of Kern
County, Highway 152 through Pacheco Pass, and Highway 41 along
the west side of the San Joaquin Valley.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 4 AM PST SUNDAY
